@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="mb-4">
    <h1 class="mb-1">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-muted">How we handle and protect your data in accordance with GDPR and HIPAA regulations.</p>
</div>

<div class="row g-4">

    <div class="col-12">
        <div class="card shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="fw-semibold mb-3">
                    <i class="bi bi-shield-lock me-2 text-primary"></i> Data Protection Overview
                </h5>
                <p>
                    This application is designed for the onboarding and adaptive training of auxiliary medical personnel,
                    including medical assistants, caregivers, receptionists, and support staff. As such, it operates
                    in an environment where sensitive personal data is routinely handled.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We are committed to ensuring that all data is processed in full compliance with
                    <strong>GDPR</strong> (General Data Protection Regulation, applicable in Europe) and
                    <strong>HIPAA</strong> (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act, applicable in the USA).
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card shadow-sm h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="fw-semibold mb-3">
                    <i class="bi bi-collection me-2 text-primary"></i> Data We Collect
                </h5>
                <p>We collect and process the following categories of data:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Full name and contact information of registered personnel</li>
                    <li>Employee type and organizational role</li>
                    <li>Training progress and course completion records</li>
                    <li>Quiz results and adaptive test scores</li>
                    <li>Profile images (optional, uploaded by the user)</li>
                    <li>Login credentials (stored securely using industry-standard hashing)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card shadow-sm h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="fw-semibold mb-3">
                    <i class="bi bi-gear me-2 text-primary"></i> How We Use Your Data
                </h5>
                <p>Your data is used exclusively for the following purposes:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Providing personalized onboarding training modules</li>
                    <li>Adaptive test generation based on demonstrated understanding</li>
                    <li>Tracking individual progress and compliance status</li>
                    <li>Generating internal progress and compliance reports</li>
                    <li>Managing employee records within your organization</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="text-muted small mt-2">
                    We do not sell, share, or use your data for any purpose outside of the above.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card shadow-sm h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="fw-semibold mb-3">
                    <i class="bi bi-eu me-2 text-primary"></i> GDPR Compliance
                </h5>
                <p>In accordance with GDPR, you have the following rights:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Right of access</strong> — you can request a copy of your personal data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> — you can correct inaccurate data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> — you can request deletion of your data</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to portability</strong> — you can export your data in a readable format</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to object</strong> — you can object to certain types of processing</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="text-muted small mt-2">
                    To exercise any of these rights, please contact your clinic administrator.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-md-6">
        <div class="card shadow-sm h-100">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="fw-semibold mb-3">
                    <i class="bi bi-hospital me-2 text-primary"></i> HIPAA Compliance
                </h5>
                <p>
                    In environments subject to HIPAA, this application supports compliance through:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Secure authentication and role-based access control</li>
                    <li>Training staff on the proper handling and storage of patient data</li>
                    <li>Ensuring personnel understand their obligations regarding Protected Health Information (PHI)</li>
                    <li>Audit-ready progress reports for internal compliance management</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="text-muted small mt-2">
                    All training content related to patient data handling is designed to meet HIPAA standards.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-12">
        <div class="card shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h5 class="fw-semibold mb-3">
                    <i class="bi bi-lock me-2 text-primary"></i> Data Security
                </h5>
                <p>
                    We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your data, including encrypted
                    password storage, secure file handling for uploaded content, and role-based access restrictions
                    to ensure that only authorized personnel can access sensitive information.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-0 text-muted small">
                    Last updated: 2026. For any privacy-related concerns, contact your clinic administrator.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>